cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.IT, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the properties of regular and context-free languages. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the behavior of languages when they need to cut numerous infinite languages, which can be seen as a problem of data structure manipulation. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper deals with the logical properties of languages and their subsets. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the dissecting power of regular languages, which can be seen as a measure of information content. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of dissecting regular languages and their subsets.
